<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-16-0908 </DOCNO><TEXT>In the early eighties the European Communities saw the need to discussshipments of radioactive substances within the EC countries, especiallyunder some aspects of the nuclear fuel cycle. Under all conditions, smoothtransport had to be ensured, e.g. from a nuclear power plant to a reprocessingplant. The Energy Directorate General of the European Communities thereforeestablished a group of experts in 1982 who were to deal with problemsassociated with shipments of radioactive substances. One of their firstmajor activities was the drafting of a report to the European Parliamentin which the situation of shipments of radioactive substances withinthe EC was examined. The results of that report are outlined in the article.</TEXT></DOC>